2026-03-22 22:50:06,022 DEBUG vector-search-filtering-metadata description: Most RAG implementations treat vector similarity as the sole retrieval signal, leading to semantically relevant but contextually wrong results—surfacing documents from the wrong tenant, time period, or permission scope. This post dives into combining ANN vector search with structured metadata predicates at query time, covering pre-filtering vs. post-filtering trade-offs, index strategies in systems like Pinecone, Weaviate, and pgvector, and the performance cliffs you'll hit at scale. The key takeaway: metadata filtering isn't a bolt-on—it fundamentally shapes your index design and query latency budget, and getting it wrong means your retrieval precision stays low no matter how good your embeddings are.
