2026-03-22 23:05:17,761 DEBUG anomaly-detection-metrics-grafana description: Most alerting setups rely on static thresholds that either miss subtle regressions or drown teams in noise — this post tackles that gap by walking through how to layer ML-based anomaly detection on top of Grafana's metrics pipeline using tools like Prophet, isolation forests, and Grafana's native alerting hooks. You'll see how to model seasonal baselines, detect drift in latency and error rate distributions, and route anomaly signals into actionable alerts without replacing your existing observability stack. The main takeaway is a practical architecture pattern that shifts your alerting from "is this over the limit?" to "is this behaving unexpectedly?" — reducing alert fatigue while catching real incidents earlier.
